hpicfPoe.name: hpicfPoe

revisions.description: Added a default type in hpicfPoePethPsePortPoePlusPowerValue.
Added a field in hpicfPoePethPsePortPoePlusPowerValue and modified the description.

Added following object,group and compliance. hpicfPoePethMainPsePdPowerDraw hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTableGroup1 hpicfPoeCompliance8 and deprecated hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTableGroup and hpicfPoeCompliance4.
Added hpicfPoePowerSupplyAuxCapacity, hpicfPoeAuxPowerSupplyGroup, hpicfPoePethPsePortLowPriority, hpicfPoeLowPowerPortGroup, hpicfPoeCompliance5. Added auxFault state to hpicfPoePowerSupplyType.

Add table for PSE Power usage features. Added following objects,group and compliance. hpicfPoePethPsePortOperStatus hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerMode hpicfPoePethPsePortAveragePower hpicfPoePethPsePortPeakPower hpicfPoePethPsePortPreStdDetect hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTable hpicfPoeMaxGuaranteedPower hpicfPoeRemainingGuaranteedPower hpicfPoePethPsePowerTable hpicfPoePethPsePowerTableGroup hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTableGroup hpicfPoePowerUsageGlobalGroup hpicfPseParamsGroup hpicfPoePethPsePortPreStdDetectGroup hpicfPoeCompliance3 hpicfPoeCompliance4 and deprecated hpicfPoeCompliance2 and hpicfPseFeaturesGroup.
Deprecate switch level pre std detect & add at port level.
Add table for PSE features, and deprecate scalar globals.
Add objects to support POE power parameters
Add objects to support POE allocation.
Add objects to support POE global characteristics.

hpicfPoe.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfPoe.description: This MIB module describes management objects that manage Power Source Equipment (PSE).

hpicfPoePethPsePortTable.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortTable
hpicfPoePethPsePortTable.description: This table supplements the table 'pethPsePortTable' in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPsePortEntry.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortEntry
hpicfPoePethPsePortEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement fields in 'pethPsePortEntry in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPsePortCurrent.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortCurrent
hpicfPoePethPsePortCurrent.description: This field specifies the current supplied at this port. This value is specified in milli amperes(mA).

hpicfPoePethPsePortVoltage.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortVoltage
hpicfPoePethPsePortVoltage.description: This field specifies the Voltage supplied at this port. This value is specified in 10's of volts (dV)

hpicfPoePethPsePortPower.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPower
hpicfPoePethPsePortPower.description: This field specifies the Power supplied at this port. This value is specified in milliwatts (mW).

hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerAllocateBy.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerAllocateBy
hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerAllocateBy.description: This field specifies the power allocation method for this port. The default value is usage.

hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerValue.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerValue
hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerValue.description: This field specifies the power allocation defined for this port. This value is specified in Watts (W).

hpicfPoePethPsePortLLDPDetect.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortLLDPDetect
hpicfPoePethPsePortLLDPDetect.description: This field specifies if power should be allocated using LLDP advertised information regarding the PD.

hpicfPoePethPsePortPoePlusPowerValue.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPoePlusPowerValue
hpicfPoePethPsePortPoePlusPowerValue.description: This field specifies the power allocation defined for this port. Use this object for equipment supporting high power, that is greater than 15 Watts. This value is specified in Watts (W). This object may only be read or written when hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerAllocateBy is set to value(3).

hpicfPoePethPsePortActualPower.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortActualPower
hpicfPoePethPsePortActualPower.description: This field specifies the actual power drained by the device connected to this port.

hpicfPoePethPsePortOperStatus.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortOperStatus
hpicfPoePethPsePortOperStatus.description: This field specifies the operational status of the port

hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerMode.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerMode
hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerMode.description: This field specifies the power mode of the port whether enabled or disabled or disableWithFiber

hpicfPoePethPsePortAveragePower.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortAveragePower
hpicfPoePethPsePortAveragePower.description: This field specifies the average power supplied to this port which is used by the device connected to it.

hpicfPoePethPsePortPeakPower.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPeakPower
hpicfPoePethPsePortPeakPower.description: This field specifies the peak power supplied to this port which is used by the device connected to it.

hpicfPoePethPsePortPreStdDetect.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPreStdDetect
hpicfPoePethPsePortPreStdDetect.description: This field specifies the pre standard detect status for this port. A value of On - indicates that power pre-802.3af-standard devices. A value of Off - indicates that only pre-802.3af/at compliant devices are allowed. The default value is Off.

hpicfPoePethPsePortLowPriority.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortLowPriority
hpicfPoePethPsePortLowPriority.description: This object indicates whether a particular port shuts down in the event of any PSU failure in the system. A value of (1) indicates a low priority port which shuts down in the event of any PSU failure. A value of (2) indicates a high priority port which is unaffected by the failure of any single PSU. The default value is high.

hpicfPoePethPsePortResetState.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortResetState
hpicfPoePethPsePortResetState.description: This object is used to reset the PoE controller HW to which the port is associated.

hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerType.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerType
hpicfPoePethPsePortPowerType.description: This field specifies the PD type determined during physical layer classification. The default value is -1.

hpicfPoeAllowPreStdDetect.name: hpicfPoeAllowPreStdDetect
hpicfPoeAllowPreStdDetect.description: This object is used to configure the default POE power detection mode. A value of TRUE - indicates that power pre-802.3af-standard devices. A value of FALSE - indicates that only pre-802.3af compliant devices are allowed. The default value is true. In a stack, this value pertains only to the commander switch.

hpicfPoePowerRedundancy.name: hpicfPoePowerRedundancy
hpicfPoePowerRedundancy.description: This object is used to configure the POE power redundancy mode. A value of none(1) - means that all available power can be allocated to powered devices. A value of nPlus1(2) - means that one of the highest power supplies is held in reserve and that in the event of a single power supply failure, no no powered devices will be shut down. A value of full(3) - means that half of the available power supplies are held in reserve. The default value is none(1). In a stack, this value pertains only to the commander switch.

hpicfPoeExtPwrSupplyCount.name: hpicfPoeExtPwrSupplyCount
hpicfPoeExtPwrSupplyCount.description: This object is used to configure the number of external power supplies expected to be connected to the chassis. The default value is 1. In a stack, this value pertains only to the commander switch.

hpicfPseFeaturesTable.name: hpicfPseFeaturesTable
hpicfPseFeaturesTable.description: This table describes the features of each power source equipment (PSE). On standalone switches (both stackable and chassis switches) there shall be only one entry in this table. In a stack, there shall be one entry for each stack member.

hpicfPseFeaturesEntry.name: hpicfPseFeaturesEntry
hpicfPseFeaturesEntry.description: A row in the PSE features table, signifying a single power source equipment.

hpicfPseAllowPreStdDetect.name: hpicfPseAllowPreStdDetect
hpicfPseAllowPreStdDetect.description: This object is used to configure the default POE power detection mode for this power source equipment. A value of TRUE - indicates that power pre-802.3af-standard devices. A value of FALSE - indicates that only pre-802.3af compliant devices are allowed. The default value is true.

hpicfPsePowerRedundancy.name: hpicfPsePowerRedundancy
hpicfPsePowerRedundancy.description: This object is used to configure the POE power redundancy mode for this power source equipment. A value of none(1) - means that all available power can be allocated to powered devices. A value of nPlus1(2) - means that one of the highest power supplies is held in reserve and that in the event of a single power supply failure, no powered devices will be shut down. A value of full(3) - means that half of the available power supplies are held in reserve. The default value is none(1).

hpicfPseExtPwrSupplyCount.name: hpicfPseExtPwrSupplyCount
hpicfPseExtPwrSupplyCount.description: This object is used to configure the number of external power supplies expected to be connected to the Power Source Equipment. The default value is 1.

hpicfPseAvailablePower.name: hpicfPseAvailablePower
hpicfPseAvailablePower.description: This field specifies the total power available on this Power source equipment. This includes internal and external power supplies.

hpicfPseUsedPower.name: hpicfPseUsedPower
hpicfPseUsedPower.description: This field specifies the total power allocated on the Power Source Equipment. This is the sum of the power allocated to all the ports on the PSE.

hpicfPseFailoverPower.name: hpicfPseFailoverPower
hpicfPseFailoverPower.description: This field specifies the failover power for this Power Source Equipment.

hpicfPseRedundantPower.name: hpicfPseRedundantPower
hpicfPseRedundantPower.description: This field specifies the redundancy POE power available to the Power Source Equipment.

hpicfPseCurrentPowerDraw.name: hpicfPseCurrentPowerDraw
hpicfPseCurrentPowerDraw.description: This field specifies the redundancy POE power available to the Power Source Equipment.

hpicfPoePowerSupplyTable.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplyTable
hpicfPoePowerSupplyTable.description: This table contains one row per power supply available to the switch.

hpicfPoePowerSupplyEntry.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplyEntry
hpicfPoePowerSupplyEntry.description: Information about a particular power supply. Each entry provides information about power supply whether it is external or internal, if it is poe/poePlus and the capacity of the power supply.

hpicfPoePowerSupplySourceType.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplySourceType
hpicfPoePowerSupplySourceType.description: This field specifies whether the power supply is external or internal. Stackable switch has inbuilt power supply and can have upto 1 external power supply. Chassis switch can have upto 2 internal power supplies for 6 slot and upto 4 for 12 slot. Chassis switch can have upto 2 external power supplies.

hpicfPoePowerSupplyType.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplyType
hpicfPoePowerSupplyType.description: This field specifies the type of the power supply, poe or poePlus.

hpicfPoePowerSupplyCapacity.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplyCapacity
hpicfPoePowerSupplyCapacity.description: This field specifies the capacity of the power supply.

hpicfPoePowerSupplyAuxCapacity.name: hpicfPoePowerSupplyAuxCapacity
hpicfPoePowerSupplyAuxCapacity.description: This MIB object specifies the capacity of the auxiliary power supply. The power supplies other than the model J9830A returns the value NULL.

hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTable.name: hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTable
hpicfPoePethPseOperStateTable.description: This table supplements the table 'pethPsePortTable' in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPseOperStateEntry.name: hpicfPoePethPseOperStateEntry
hpicfPoePethPseOperStateEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement fields in 'pethPsePortEntry in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPseOperState.name: hpicfPoePethPseOperState
hpicfPoePethPseOperState.description: This field specifies the operation status. The default value is on.

hpicfPoePethPsePortNum.name: hpicfPoePethPsePortNum
hpicfPoePethPsePortNum.description: This field specifies the port number.

hpicfPoePethMainPsePdPowerDraw.name: hpicfPoePethMainPsePdPowerDraw
hpicfPoePethMainPsePdPowerDraw.description: This field specifies the total actual power that is used by all the ports on this slot or member.

hpicfPoeMaxGuaranteedPower.name: hpicfPoeMaxGuaranteedPower
hpicfPoeMaxGuaranteedPower.description: This field specifies the guaranteed maximum PoE power, namely, the maximum power supplied to critical PSEs

hpicfPoeRemainingGuaranteedPower.name: hpicfPoeRemainingGuaranteedPower
hpicfPoeRemainingGuaranteedPower.description: This field specifies the Remaining Guaranteed power. This is difference of Guaranteed Maximum PoE Power and the sum of maximum power of critical PSEs

hpicfPoePethPsePowerTable.name: hpicfPoePethPsePowerTable
hpicfPoePethPsePowerTable.description: This table supplements the table 'pethPsePortTable' in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPsePowerEntry.name: hpicfPoePethPsePowerEntry
hpicfPoePethPsePowerEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement fields in pethPsePortEntry in ieee802af.mib.

hpicfPoePethPsePeakPower.name: hpicfPoePethPsePeakPower
hpicfPoePethPsePeakPower.description: This field specifies the peak power of the PSE.

hpicfPoePethPseAvgPower.name: hpicfPoePethPseAvgPower
hpicfPoePethPseAvgPower.description: This field specifies the average power of the PSE.
